rComments: Richard Bozec is a good teacher. However, the course is ansynchronous so you should get ready to read. It is really important to buy his book as soon as the semester starts. Also, do ALL the exercices and don't procrastinate because there's a lot of things to learn. The exams are pretty fair and if you study enough you should get a good grade.

Très bon prof . Il faut acheter son livre dans lequel il y a que des power points , mais cela s'est très bien passé. Faites les exercices il se basent la dessus pour ses examens. Examen à livre ouvert.
Excellent prof. Easy lecture and tests. But you have to buy an expensive text book he wrote. (open-book exams)

He's a great prof but my course was entirely asynchronous. With that said, the textbook was mandatory as we needed the problems to submit every week online. However, his exams were very fair and the course was well structured.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'So many papers', 'Lots of homework']

rComments: Très bon prof qui explique super sa matière. Son livre est vraiment utile puisquil se base sur ses exercices pour lexamen. Néanmoins il ne permet pas lutilisation de son pc durant son cours. Je le reprendrais avec plaisir !

Pas le droit aux écrans à son cours, ça choque au début mais on s'y habitue :) Il est très à l'écoute (il a accepté de revoir et re-noter l'un de mes devoirs) , très ponctuel il n'accepte pas les retards.
Really straight forward and clear. The prof was great when it came to explaining concepts. Course pack was also really helpful.

Lectures aren't the most entertaining, the midterm is pretty light but the final is difficult. The book is a scam but buy it anyways or you will probably fail. Do the exercises at the end of each chapter and you should be okay.

Forces you to buy his course pack ($150 btw) which consists of his powerpoint slides in order to have a chance to keep up with the material. Disallows all forms of technology (including laptops to take notes) meaning you're left with pencil and paper for notes. In addition, he also goes over his slides way too fast to properly digest the material.

His powerpoints have no information according to himself. You need to buy his book (of course) to get the notes. Teaches in a very outdated and inefficient fashion, banning all laptops from his class. This simply does not work for me and I dropped his class after a day lol.

At first glance Bozec seems kinda rude (doesn't accept anyone that arrives 5 mins late & doesn't allow any phones or computers). He also makes you pay 100$ + for a book that HE wrote lol. BUT, he is very knowledgable and honestly wants his students to pass. He describes specifically what is on midterm and final. The exams are very fair

awful prof who doesn't care about his students. not to mention he makes everyone pay for his stupid "textbook" which consists solely of powerpoint slides. if you want a prof who speeds through powerpoint slides, is extremely condescending and rude, take Bozec.

Pretty terrible prof. Makes you spend 140+$ on his OWN book and then has the audacity to say "I don't know how much it costs" when asked. He speeds through his slides so keep up with the homework at the end of every chapter and you'll be good. DO THE WORK ACCORDINGLY. It is so easy to fall behind and since it's a heavy subject, keep yourself busy.
Il n'apparait pas comme la personne la plus sympathique mais il est très compétent, accessible et ses examens sont justes. Un bon prof pour la comptabilité.

such a bad prof. he speeds through all of his power point slides and it is very hard to keep up and actually learn. his exams are very difficult. he is very rude to students who ask questions in his class. you also have to buy a 140$ textbook composed of POWER POINT SLIDES in order to pass his class. awful prof. he is so bad at explaining.
lazy, forces you to spend 140 dollars on the printed versions of his powerpoint slides, which takes up to 700 pages which you have to read all of in order to study for the final exam

Vous devez assister au cours pour comprendre et lenseignant et sévère par rapport à la technologie et aux retards. Cependant il explique bien même si cest parfois un peu long. Lexamen final est seulement composé de QCM.
Made financial accounting understandable for students who have never taken accounting classes before to make it easy for you to understand the basic concepts

Nice prof, goes through material fairly quickly so make sure you keep up. Get the course pack and keep up with the homework or else you might fall behind. Lots of things to remember, you have to study quite a bit to get the concepts but the midterm and final are both fair.

He's done a great job at structuring the class in a manner which allows students to easily digest the material. The midterm, assignment, and exam were very fair; no tricks. Know the stuff and you'll do well. It's tough to catch up if you don't keep up with the readings given the cumulative nature of the subject. Do the exercise and test bank Qs

His classes are very straightforward and easy to understand. The material seems simple but exams were more difficult. Do the review questions and test bank questions. Very easy class for some, more difficult for others. If the midterm is open book write everything from the slides in yours.
Awesome teacher
Hands down best teacher at Telfer. He's straight up right from the beginning, tells you what to read and what not to read and his exams have no surprises, got an A in his class.
Professeur très compétent, il explique très bien la matière et désire que ses étudiants réussissent.
boring, confusing
